<dl id="n10076i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10076i">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10076i"> 76(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> wooden walls</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Th&eacute;mistocle, qui a &eacute;t&eacute; peut-&ecirc;tre le plus habile des d&eacute;fenseurs de la Gr&egrave;ce, et qui avait, le premier, compris le sens de l&apos;oracle conseillant aux Ath&eacute;niens de se r&eacute;fugier derri&egrave;re des <mark>murailles de bois</mark>, c&apos;est&agrave;- dire sur leurs vaisseaux, Th&eacute;mistocle eut un go&ucirc;t particulier pour les messages secrets <font color="green">[Themistocles&mdash;who was perhaps the most skilful defender of Greece and who had been the first to understand the meaning of the Oracle&apos;s advice to the Athenians to take refuge behind wooden walls, that is to say within their ships&mdash;was particularly fond of secret messages]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
